\section{Mayer-Vietoris LES technical heart: four auxiliary lemmas + sequence iso (iter-023)}

After Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequence} the Mayer-Vietoris LES sequence is packaged in the standard $\mathtt{ComposableArrows}$-form. Iter-023 lays the \emph{technical heart} of the LES: the comparison iso $\HModulePrime\_\mathtt{sequenceIso}$ from the iter-022 sequence to Mathlib's $\Ext.\mathtt{contravariantSequence}$ (file \texttt{Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/DerivedCategory/Ext/ExactSequences.lean}), mirroring Mathlib \texttt{MayerVietoris.lean} L124--138 line-by-line for the $\ModuleCat\,k$ flavor. The construction requires four substantial auxiliary lemmas (Mathlib L48--106) bridging the $\AddCommGrpCat$-side $\mathtt{biprodIsoProd}$ machinery (where the cohomology presheaf actually lives, courtesy of the iter-016 codomain choice $C^{op} \to \AddCommGrpCat$) and the $\Ext$-side $\Ext.\mathtt{biprodAddEquiv}$.

\subsection{Four auxiliary lemmas (Mathlib L48--106 mirrors)}

\begin{lemma}[$\toBiprod$ explicit elementwise formula (iter-023)]
  \label{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_toBiprod_apply}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule'_toBiprod_apply}
  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_toBiprod, def:Scheme_HModule_prime_cohomologyPresheaf}
  Let $k$, $C$, $J$, $S$, $F$, $n$ be as in Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_toBiprod}. For any $y \in \HModulePrime\_\cohomologyPresheaf\,k\,F\,n\,(\op\,S.X_4)$,
  \[
    \HModulePrime\_\toBiprod\,k\,S\,F\,n\,(y) \;=\; (\AddCommGrpCat.\mathtt{biprodIsoProd}\,\_\,\_).\mathrm{inv}\,\langle (\HModulePrime\_\cohomologyPresheaf\,k\,F\,n).\mathrm{map}\,S.f_{2,4}^{op}\,y, (\HModulePrime\_\cohomologyPresheaf\,k\,F\,n).\mathrm{map}\,S.f_{3,4}^{op}\,y \rangle.
  \]
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_toBiprod}
  Direct mirror of Mathlib's $\mathtt{toBiprod\_apply}$ (\texttt{MayerVietoris.lean} L48--64). The proof bridges via $(\AddCommGrpCat.\mathtt{biprodIsoProd}).\mathtt{addCommGroupIsoToAddEquiv}$'s injectivity, then $\mathtt{ext}$ on the two biproduct components, then closes each side by the $\mathtt{biprodIsoProd}$-vs-$\mathtt{biprod.lift}$ identities. Every step is value-category-agnostic and transfers cleanly. Plan-agent \texttt{lean\_run\_code} probe (iter-023) confirms the body typechecks end-to-end, kernel-only axioms.
\end{proof}

\begin{lemma}[$\fromBiprod$ explicit elementwise formula (iter-023)]
  \label{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_fromBiprod_biprodIsoProd_inv_apply}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule'_fromBiprod_biprodIsoProd_inv_apply}
  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_fromBiprod, def:Scheme_HModule_prime_cohomologyPresheaf}
  Let $k$, $C$, $J$, $S$, $F$, $n$ be as in Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_fromBiprod}. For any $y_1 \in \HModulePrime\_\cohomologyPresheaf\,k\,F\,n\,(\op\,S.X_2)$ and $y_2 \in \HModulePrime\_\cohomologyPresheaf\,k\,F\,n\,(\op\,S.X_3)$,
  \[
    \HModulePrime\_\fromBiprod\,k\,S\,F\,n\,((\AddCommGrpCat.\mathtt{biprodIsoProd}\,\_\,\_).\mathrm{inv}\,\langle y_1, y_2 \rangle) \;=\; (\HModulePrime\_\cohomologyPresheaf\,k\,F\,n).\mathrm{map}\,S.f_{1,2}^{op}\,y_1 - (\HModulePrime\_\cohomologyPresheaf\,k\,F\,n).\mathrm{map}\,S.f_{1,3}^{op}\,y_2.
  \]
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_fromBiprod}
  Direct mirror of Mathlib's $\mathtt{fromBiprod\_biprodIsoProd\_inv\_apply}$ (\texttt{MayerVietoris.lean} L77--83). The body is a one-liner: \lstinline{dsimp [HModule'_fromBiprod]; rw [← ConcreteCategory.comp_apply]; simp [AddCommGrpCat.biprodIsoProd_inv_comp_desc, sub_eq_add_neg]}. Plan-agent \texttt{lean\_run\_code} probe (iter-023) confirms.
\end{proof}

\begin{lemma}[$\Ext$-side / $\AddCommGrpCat$-side bridge for $\toBiprod$ (iter-023)]
  \label{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_biprodAddEquiv_symm_biprodIsoProd_hom_toBiprod_apply}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule'_biprodAddEquiv_symm_biprodIsoProd_hom_toBiprod_apply}
  \uses{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_toBiprod_apply, def:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex}
  Let $k$, $C$, $J$, $S$, $F$, $n$ be as above. For any $x \in \HModulePrime\_\cohomologyPresheaf\,k\,F\,n\,(\op\,S.X_4)$,
  \[
    \Ext.\mathtt{biprodAddEquiv}^{-1}\,((\AddCommGrpCat.\mathtt{biprodIsoProd}\,\_\,\_).\mathrm{hom}\,(\HModulePrime\_\toBiprod\,k\,S\,F\,n\,x)) \;=\; (\Ext.\mathtt{mk_0}\,(\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex\,k\,S).g).\mathtt{comp}\,x\,(\mathtt{zero\_add}\,n).
  \]
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  \uses{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_toBiprod_apply}
  Direct mirror of Mathlib's $\mathtt{biprodAddEquiv\_symm\_biprodIsoProd\_hom\_toBiprod\_apply}$ (\texttt{MayerVietoris.lean} L85--91). Body: \lstinline{Ext.biprodAddEquiv.injective (by cat_disch)}. Requires the wrapper attributes $\mathtt{set\_option}$ \lstinline{backward.isDefEq.respectTransparency false in} (relaxes typeclass-search transparency, mirrors Mathlib L85) followed by $\mathtt{attribute}$ \lstinline{[local simp] HModule'_toBiprod_apply in} (registers Lemma~\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_toBiprod_apply} as a local $\mathtt{simp}$ lemma so $\mathtt{cat\_disch}$ can use it, mirrors Mathlib L86). Plan-agent \texttt{lean\_run\_code} probe (iter-023) confirms.
\end{proof}

\begin{lemma}[$\Ext$-side / $\AddCommGrpCat$-side bridge for $\fromBiprod$ (iter-023)]
  \label{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_mk0_f_comp_biprodAddEquiv_symm_biprodIsoProd_hom}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule'_mk₀_f_comp_biprodAddEquiv_symm_biprodIsoProd_hom}
  \uses{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_fromBiprod_biprodIsoProd_inv_apply, def:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex}
  Let $k$, $C$, $J$, $S$, $F$, $n$ be as above. For any $x \in \HModulePrime\_\cohomologyPresheaf\,k\,F\,n\,(\op\,S.X_2) \boxplus \HModulePrime\_\cohomologyPresheaf\,k\,F\,n\,(\op\,S.X_3)$,
  \[
    (\Ext.\mathtt{mk_0}\,(\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex\,k\,S).f).\mathtt{comp}\,(\Ext.\mathtt{biprodAddEquiv}^{-1}\,((\AddCommGrpCat.\mathtt{biprodIsoProd}\,\_\,\_).\mathrm{hom}\,x))\,(\mathtt{zero\_add}\,n) \;=\; \HModulePrime\_\fromBiprod\,k\,S\,F\,n\,x.
  \]
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  \uses{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_fromBiprod_biprodIsoProd_inv_apply}
  Direct mirror of Mathlib's $\mathtt{mk_0\_f\_comp\_biprodAddEquiv\_symm\_biprodIsoProd\_hom}$ (\texttt{MayerVietoris.lean} L93--106). Body: \lstinline{obtain ⟨⟨x₂, x₃⟩, rfl⟩ := (AddCommGrpCat.biprodIsoProd _ _).addCommGroupIsoToAddEquiv.symm.surjective x; dsimp; rw [Ext.biprodAddEquiv_symm_apply, Iso.addCommGroupIsoToAddEquiv_symm_apply, HModule'_fromBiprod_biprodIsoProd_inv_apply]; cat_disch}. Requires the wrapper attributes $\mathtt{set\_option}$ \lstinline{backward.isDefEq.respectTransparency false in} (mirrors Mathlib L93) and $\mathtt{attribute}$ \lstinline{[local simp] sub_eq_add_neg in} (registers $\mathtt{sub\_eq\_add\_neg}$ as a local $\mathtt{simp}$ lemma to close the additive-inverse step, mirrors Mathlib L94). Plan-agent \texttt{lean\_run\_code} probe (iter-023) confirms.
\end{proof}

\subsection{Sequence iso (Mathlib L124--138 mirror) --- the technical heart}

\begin{definition}[Mayer-Vietoris LES sequence iso (iter-023)]
  \label{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequenceIso}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule'_sequenceIso}
  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequence, lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_biprodAddEquiv_symm_biprodIsoProd_hom_toBiprod_apply, lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_mk0_f_comp_biprodAddEquiv_symm_biprodIsoProd_hom, lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex_shortExact}
  Let $k$, $C$, $J$, $S$, $F$, $n_0, n_1, h$ be as in Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequence}. The \emph{comparison iso} from the Mayer-Vietoris LES sequence to the contravariant Ext sequence is the iso
  \[
    \HModulePrime\_\mathtt{sequenceIso}\,k\,S\,F\,n_0\,n_1\,h \;:\; \HModulePrime\_\mathtt{sequence}\,k\,S\,F\,n_0\,n_1\,h \;\cong\; \Ext.\mathtt{contravariantSequence}\,(\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex\_\mathtt{shortExact}\,k\,S)\,F\,n_0\,n_1\,(\mathtt{by\ omega})
  \]
  in $\mathrm{Iso}\,(\mathtt{ComposableArrows}\,\AddCommGrpCat\,5)$, mirroring Mathlib's $\mathtt{GrothendieckTopology.MayerVietorisSquare.sequenceIso}$ (\texttt{MayerVietoris.lean} L124--138) line-by-line for the $\ModuleCat\,k$ flavor.
\end{definition}

\begin{proof}
  \uses{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_biprodAddEquiv_symm_biprodIsoProd_hom_toBiprod_apply, lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_mk0_f_comp_biprodAddEquiv_symm_biprodIsoProd_hom}
  Direct mirror of Mathlib's $\mathtt{sequenceIso}$ (\texttt{MayerVietoris.lean} L124--138). The body is a $\mathtt{ComposableArrows.isoMk_5}$ constructor invocation taking six iso fields (alternating $\mathtt{Iso.refl}$ and $(\AddCommGrpCat.\mathtt{biprodIsoProd}\,\_\,\_).\mathtt{trans}\,(\Ext.\mathtt{biprodAddEquiv}^{-1}).\mathtt{toAddCommGrpIso}$) and five $2$-cell coherence proofs:
  \begin{itemize}
    \item Squares $0$ and $3$ (the $\toBiprod$ squares at $n_0$ and $n_1$): \lstinline{by ext; apply HModule'_biprodAddEquiv_symm_biprodIsoProd_hom_toBiprod_apply} (Lemma~\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_biprodAddEquiv_symm_biprodIsoProd_hom_toBiprod_apply});
    \item Squares $1$ and $4$ (the $\fromBiprod$ squares at $n_0$ and $n_1$): \lstinline{by ext; symm; apply HModule'_mk₀_f_comp_biprodAddEquiv_symm_biprodIsoProd_hom} (Lemma~\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_mk0_f_comp_biprodAddEquiv_symm_biprodIsoProd_hom});
    \item Square $2$ (the central $\delta$ square): \lstinline{by dsimp; rw [Category.comp_id, Category.id_comp]; rfl} --- the iso component is $\mathtt{Iso.refl}$, so the square reduces to a categorical identity.
  \end{itemize}
  Requires the wrapper attribute $\mathtt{set\_option}$ \lstinline{backward.isDefEq.respectTransparency false in} (mirrors Mathlib L124).

  Note the only deviation from Mathlib's idiom: the file's $\open\,\mathtt{CategoryTheory\,Limits\,TopologicalSpace\,AlgebraicGeometry}$ does \emph{not} include $\mathtt{Category}$, so the central square uses qualified $\mathtt{Category.comp\_id}$ / $\mathtt{Category.id\_comp}$ instead of Mathlib's bare $\mathtt{comp\_id}$ / $\mathtt{id\_comp}$ (which require Mathlib's $\open\,\mathtt{Category}$ at L32). The body is otherwise identical to Mathlib's. Plan-agent \texttt{lean\_run\_code} probe (iter-023) confirms.
\end{proof}

\begin{remark}[Why iter-023 is one substantial iteration (5 declarations)]
  Mathlib L48--138 packs four auxiliary lemmas plus the comparison iso into a tightly-coupled cohort: the iso uses lemmas 3 (\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_biprodAddEquiv_symm_biprodIsoProd_hom_toBiprod_apply}) and 4 (\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_mk0_f_comp_biprodAddEquiv_symm_biprodIsoProd_hom}) twice each (once each for the $n_0$ and $n_1$ squares), and lemmas 3, 4 in turn use lemmas 1 and 2 (\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_toBiprod_apply}, \ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_fromBiprod_biprodIsoProd_inv_apply}) as local $\mathtt{simp}$ rewrites and verbatim invocations respectively. Splitting the cohort across two iterations would force iter-024 (or beyond) to re-establish the full iter-023 lemma context before scaffolding the iso, doubling the prover's setup cost. Iter-023 instead lays the entire cohort in one substantial iteration --- matching the iter-020 precedent of 5 declarations in one round (helper instance + Mono + Epi + Exact + ShortExact) for a tightly-coupled cohort.

  Iter-024 then closes the LES proper with three short one-liners on top of iter-023: the exactness theorem $\HModulePrime\_\mathtt{sequence\_exact}$ via $\mathtt{exact\_of\_iso}$ (one-liner), and the $\delta\_\toBiprod$ / $\fromBiprod\_\delta$ $\mathtt{simp}$ companions via $.\mathtt{zero}\,2$ / $.\mathtt{zero}\,1$ (one-liner each). The Mathlib gap surfaced is none: every step is value-category-agnostic for the $\AddCommGrpCat$-flavored carrier (forced by the iter-016 $\HModulePrime\_\cohomologyPresheaf$ codomain choice).

  Iter-023 sorry-count trajectory: $9 \to 14 \to 9$ (five new \lstinline{sorry} sites in the four lemmas + iso; all filled in the iter-023 prover round).
\end{remark}

